BRAKE VACUUM CONTROL (BVC) (DIAGNOSTICS)
Step Check Yes No
1 CHECK CONNECTOR.
Check the status of the brake vacuum sensor
and brake vacuum pump connection.
Are the brake vacuum sensor
and brake vacuum pump con-
nected firmly?
Go to step 2. Connect the con-
nector.
2 CHECK FUSE.
1) Turn the ignition switch to OFF.
2) Remove the brake vacuum pump fuse.
3) Check the condition of fuse.
Is the fuse blown out? Replace the fuse. Go to step 3.
3 CHECK BRAKE VACUUM PUMP RELAY.
1) Turn the ignition switch to OFF.
2) Remove the brake vacuum pump relay from
relay box.
3) Connect the battery to the brake vacuum
pump relay terminals No. 5 and No. 8.
4) Measure the resistance between brake vac-
uum pump relay terminals.
Terminals
No. 6 — No. 7:
Is the resistance less than 1 Ω? Go to step 4. Replace the brake
vacuum pump
